               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; &#xD;
the word mǝʿǝraf;&#xD;
a few lines (in both columns) in the incipit page of each text, divided into two, three or four groups, alternating with black lines (2 lines in fol. 6r, 9 lines on fol. 44r, 5 lines on fol. 64r, 8 lines on fol. 101r); the Canon tables; &#xD;
the incipits of the parts of the Introduction (fols. 6ra – 13va) and of the chapters of the Gospels;&#xD;
the title of each Gospel; the chapters titles;&#xD;
Ethiopic numerals of the “tituli”;&#xD;
the horizontal dashes above and below Ethiopic numerals; &#xD;
elements of the punctuation signs;&#xD;
name of Wälättä Mädḫǝn, one of the donors(fol. 43vb, l.22); names of the church feasts in the upper margin of some fols. indicating the Gospel readings.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>The quire marks are misplaced; the quiremarks from 7 (፯) to 13 (፲፫) are written by a different hand.</note>
                     <note>Concerning the introduction, the contents and the postscript of the Gospels, cp. R. ZUURMOND, Novum Testamentum Aethiopice: the Synoptic Gospels, Part I: General Introduction, Part II: Edition of the Gospel of Mark, Stuttgart 1989 (AeF 27), 1-31.</note>
                     <note>The content of the last leaf (fol. 12ra – rb [l.6]) of the “Canon Tables” is summarizing the full text of the Canons Table without columns.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
